The vulnerability is described as an "incomplete blacklist vulnerability" in the context of file uploads. Specifically, it allows remote authenticated users to upload files with a `.pht` extension, which can be executed as PHP code on the server. This is a significant security risk because it can lead to arbitrary code execution.

